  "@id": "ocp:github/hankbesser--recursive-agents",
  "meta": {
    "title": "Recursive Agents",
    "description": "A meta-framework for self-improving LLMs with transparent reasoning",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-09T11:14:57.422Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-09T11:14:57.422Z",
    "keywords": [
      "ai",
      "langchain",
      "llm",
      "recursion",
      "recursive",
      "self-improvement"
    ],
    "license": "MIT"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "| Code Pattern | Why It Matters |\n|--------------|----------------|\n| **`Draft\\|LLM → Critique\\|LLM → Revision\\|LLM` chains built once** | Three-phase self-improvement is automatic - no manual wiring |\n| **One `protocol_context.txt` feeds all system prompts** | Change reasoning style everywhere with one edit | \n| **Templates live as `.txt` files on disk** | Git tracks prompt changes; hot-reload without restarting |\n| **New expert domain = inherit BaseCompanion + point to template** | Three lines of code gets you a complete agent | \n| **Every Companion instance  is itself an `agent()` or `RunnableLambda(agent)`** | Same object works standalone or in any framework | \n| **Built-in `run_log` tracks all iterations** | See why decisions were made without adding instrumentation |",
    "context": "[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)\n[![Contributing](https://img.shields.io/badge/Contributing-Guidelines-blue.svg)](CONTRIBUTING.md)",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
